    <text id="A2912T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>In this short letter to his brother, Henry requests Enos to buy cloth and
                    exchange money in Richmond.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient">Mr Enos Ott<lb/>Care Rev Henry Brown<lb/>Camp Lee<lb/>Richmond<lb/>Virginia</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1864-11-28">Nov 28/64</date>
                        <name type="place">Camp 4 <abbr expan="miles">mi</abbr> West from New Market</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear Brother</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I wrote you a line &amp; enclosed with a letter from Margaret but thinking
                    you might fail to get it I <orig reg="shall">shal</orig> again write I wish you
                    to purchase 80 to 120 <abbr expan="yards">yds</abbr>
                    <abbr expan="good">gd</abbr> cotton cloth I also wish you to exchange $1000 for
                    Gold you can check on the Bank in the name of H &amp; E Ott <abbr
                        expan="Misters">Mess</abbr> Tyler &amp; son will assist you, you will
                    also have to <del hand="h1">get</del> check for enough in addition to the $1000
                    to pay for the cotton cloth buy so cheap as you can in buying a good article
                    also if you buy or have bought the Beaver cloth for Margaret &amp; Jinnie
                    the mail is leaving &amp; I must close.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Your Brother</salute>
                    <signed>Henry Ott</signed>
                    <seg type="postscript">Write to me at Home &amp; request them to sent it to
                        me H. Ott</seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
